atives Build and develop relationships outside of CBB to influence change and/or decision making in Operations, Risk & Compliance, Chief Strategy Office and Technology Institute annual routines and standards for leadership team deliverables. Key Stakeholder Relationships Strong partnership with senior leadership teams across Operations, Technology and the Chief Strategy Office. Partner with Internal/External Audit, Risk (FLOD/SLOD) and control functions to monitor and evaluate ongoing effectiveness across CBB. Work with regulatory functions to stay well-informed of industry best practices. #LI-SB1 Qualifications Education oBachelor's Degree or equivalent work experience oMBA preferred Experience o10-15 years of experience in financial services organization, preferably banking. oProven track record of partnering with Senior leaders and driving results oExperience organizing and directing multiple teams and departments oLarge scale project management experience oProcess re-engineering experience with a willingness to roll up sleeves oStrong analytical capabilities to \u201ctell a story\u201d with data oExcellent written and verbal presentation skills Job :Business Analysis Primary Location :Massachusetts-BOSTON-75 State Street - 06366 - State Street-Corp Organization :Consumer & Business Banking (1001) Schedule :Full-time Job Posting :Jun 30, 2020, 4:04:50 PM "
